cs.CV, cs.RO, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.GR 

This paper deals with camera pose estimation, which is a problem in computer vision. The techniques used in the paper involve matching images, establishing correspondences between keypoints, and using regression forests. These are all common techniques used in computer vision, which falls under the cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition) category. Additionally, the paper deals with real-time camera pose estimation, which involves robotics and control, which falls under the cs.RO (Robotics) category. The paper also involves tuning parameters and selecting the most promising hypotheses, which involves machine learning and optimization, falling under the cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) categories. Finally, the paper involves visualizing the internal behavior of the forests, which involves graphics and visualization, falling under the cs.GR (Computer Graphics) category.
